764
00:44:13,468 --> 00:44:14,531
What is that?

765
00:44:14,968 --> 00:44:17,721
There isn't a single thing that
has been decided for sure in life.

766
00:44:20,322 --> 00:44:22,196
You're not asking for my permission.

767
00:44:23,131 --> 00:44:24,632
You're just informing me.

768
00:44:27,133 --> 00:44:28,266
I'm not informing you.

769
00:44:28,601 --> 00:44:30,441
I won't return to work
without your permission.

770
00:44:52,334 --> 00:44:53,768
It's gone bad.

771
00:45:19,328 --> 00:45:20,787
What is this?

772
00:45:20,872 --> 00:45:22,554
Breakfast is my responsibility.

773
00:45:23,000 --> 00:45:23,729
Cooking?

774
00:45:24,555 --> 00:45:26,616
I'm a great cook.

775
00:45:26,701 --> 00:45:27,768
When you come back to
Korea during your vacation...

776
00:45:27,868 --> 00:45:28,948
...I'll grill you some mackerel.

777
00:45:29,033 --> 00:45:32,166
I'm amazing at grilling mackerels.

778
00:45:32,267 --> 00:45:34,382
Soyun. He's totally lying.
You should try a video call.

779
00:45:34,467 --> 00:45:35,934
Move away.

780
00:45:36,000 --> 00:45:38,968
There's a fire. There's fire.

781
00:45:40,843 --> 00:45:43,541
"Hongjoo's dream, Jaechan's dream,
My dream"

782
00:45:49,099 --> 00:45:50,531
Do you usually have breakfast here?

783
00:45:50,616 --> 00:45:51,708
What are you doing here?

784
00:45:51,949 --> 00:45:54,001
I made some toast, but I burnt them.

785
00:45:54,100 --> 00:45:55,369
So, I was going to
have this as my breakfast.

786
00:45:55,454 --> 00:45:56,534
What about you?

787
00:45:56,619 --> 00:45:58,249
I'm in a similar situation.

788
00:45:58,801 --> 00:46:00,591
I wanted to ask you a question.

789
00:46:01,042 --> 00:46:01,888
What is it?

790
00:46:02,300 --> 00:46:03,999
That car accident back then.

791
00:46:04,767 --> 00:46:07,932
I felt really strange
when the accident happened.

792
00:46:10,638 --> 00:46:12,851
You clearly saved me from
the accident...

793
00:46:13,176 --> 00:46:14,660
...but strangely...

794
00:46:15,283 --> 00:46:17,617
...the moment before I felt like I was
dying after getting hit by the car.

795
00:46:19,740 --> 00:46:24,281
That feeling was unbelievably real.

796
00:46:26,085 --> 00:46:27,938
Did you ever experience
something like that?

797
00:46:28,334 --> 00:46:31,340
The experience of surviving
from almost dying?

798
00:46:33,303 --> 00:46:34,235
I do.

799
00:46:34,501 --> 00:46:35,365
Really?

800
00:46:35,780 --> 00:46:36,581
When?

801
00:46:37,347 --> 00:46:39,414
It was when I was really young.

802
00:46:39,499 --> 00:46:40,998
I fell in the water once.

803
00:46:41,470 --> 00:46:43,801
But someone saved me.

804
00:46:49,300 --> 00:46:52,440
I was saved because of that person,
but strangely...

805
00:46:54,053 --> 00:46:56,614
...I felt like I was drowning.

806
00:46:57,106 --> 00:46:58,336
It felt so real.

807
00:47:01,440 --> 00:47:02,640
I knew it.

808
00:47:03,382 --> 00:47:04,985
Was the person who saved you...

809
00:47:06,288 --> 00:47:07,666
...happen to be Nam Hongjoo?

810
00:47:07,751 --> 00:47:08,500
Excuse me?

811
00:47:08,585 --> 00:47:10,821
What if we look at it this way?

812
00:47:11,115 --> 00:47:13,582
I was really thankful to
you because of that feeling.

813
00:47:13,667 --> 00:47:15,536
I could've really be dead.

814
00:47:15,669 --> 00:47:18,669
I thought,
"I want to repay him for saving me."

815
00:47:18,938 --> 00:47:20,871
-Because of that thought...
-Because of that thought?

816
00:47:21,467 --> 00:47:22,940
I started having the dreams.

817
00:47:23,574 --> 00:47:26,477
I see the future of the one
who saved me in my dreams.

818
00:47:27,511 --> 00:47:29,549
You dream about Nam Hongjoo.

819
00:47:29,634 --> 00:47:32,673
So, the one who saved
you was Nam Hongjoo.

820
00:47:33,865 --> 00:47:34,733
What do you think?

821
00:47:35,167 --> 00:47:36,670
That's impossible.

822
00:47:36,834 --> 00:47:37,601
Why?

823
00:47:37,801 --> 00:47:40,834
The one who saved me was a man.
It wasn't Nam Hongjoo.

824
00:47:40,934 --> 00:47:41,866
Are you sure?

825
00:47:41,951 --> 00:47:43,392
Yes. I'm positive.

826
00:47:44,790 --> 00:47:48,052
The one who saved me was called Bamtol
and he was a boy who loved baseball.

827
00:47:48,388 --> 00:47:50,388
And he was strong and energetic.

828
00:47:54,267 --> 00:47:55,771
I'm back.

829
00:47:56,000 --> 00:47:59,074
Mom. There was a sale on
vitamins on my way back.

830
00:47:59,701 --> 00:48:00,669
Mom.

831
00:48:01,522 --> 00:48:03,089
Where did she go at this hour?

832
00:48:12,634 --> 00:48:14,849
Is this considered as food waste?

833
00:48:16,701 --> 00:48:17,822
Is that perhaps...

834
00:48:19,868 --> 00:48:21,635
Is it the mackerel that I gave you?

835
00:48:23,224 --> 00:48:25,667
No. This is...

836
00:48:25,868 --> 00:48:28,202
Grilling this was harder that I thought.

837
00:48:28,300 --> 00:48:29,734
It was difficult to control the heat too.

838
00:48:30,726 --> 00:48:34,249
Why don't you just have breakfast
at my house from now on?

839
00:48:34,334 --> 00:48:35,461
No. That's okay.

840
00:48:35,546 --> 00:48:38,035
It's because I have
a favor to ask of you.

841
00:48:38,775 --> 00:48:45,096
You don't know why Hongjoo
quit being a reporter, do you?

842
00:48:47,880 --> 00:48:51,098
She dreamt that she died as a reporter.

843
00:48:51,501 --> 00:48:54,172
That's why I told her to quit
being a reporter immediately.

844
00:48:54,906 --> 00:48:55,784
You know, don't you?

845
00:48:56,214 --> 00:48:58,952
That Hongjoo's dreams are special.

846
00:48:59,701 --> 00:49:00,998
Yes. I know.

847
00:49:02,033 --> 00:49:05,576
But that rotten girl wants to
return to work in the end.

848
00:49:06,234 --> 00:49:07,924
I should've tried to stop her.

849
00:49:15,045 --> 00:49:17,801
But I gave her permission
because I felt so bad for her.

850
00:49:19,246 --> 00:49:23,534
I felt bad for her because she wasn't
doing what she wants to do in life.

851
00:49:47,324 --> 00:49:48,556
Anyway...

852
00:49:48,769 --> 00:49:51,584
What do you like to eat, Prosecutor Jung?

853
00:49:51,801 --> 00:49:57,135
I worked at Korean, Chinese,
Western and all sorts of restaurants.

854
00:49:57,220 --> 00:49:59,544
So I can make all kinds of food.

855
00:50:00,000 --> 00:50:01,452
So just tell me.

856
00:50:01,537 --> 00:50:05,773
I'll make what you and your
brother likes every morning.

857
00:50:05,858 --> 00:50:07,756
For free. It will be free.

858
00:50:07,841 --> 00:50:08,620
Gosh.

859
00:50:08,934 --> 00:50:11,201
But why do you want to make me breakfast?

860
00:50:12,167 --> 00:50:14,634
It's because I'm thankful
to you for everything.

861
00:50:14,719 --> 00:50:16,868
I heard that you saved
my daughter several times.

862
00:50:17,434 --> 00:50:19,201
I wanted to repay you.

863
00:50:20,490 --> 00:50:24,435
And... I might be
indebted to you again.

864
00:50:27,761 --> 00:50:28,807
Well...

865
00:50:29,567 --> 00:50:31,610
I shouldn't be asking you this.

866
00:50:32,125 --> 00:50:34,435
But if something happens...

867
00:50:35,367 --> 00:50:37,241
...please protect my daughter.

868
00:51:08,199 --> 00:51:10,934
Should I return to work or not?

869
00:51:12,901 --> 00:51:14,335
It wasn't because she didn't want to.

870
00:51:15,934 --> 00:51:18,768
She wanted to, but she was scared.

871
00:51:52,267 --> 00:51:53,903
Face expressions are so mysterious.

872
00:51:55,501 --> 00:51:56,568
Let's do it!

873
00:51:57,367 --> 00:51:58,262
Let's do it!

874
00:51:59,234 --> 00:52:00,097
Let's do it!

875
00:52:00,367 --> 00:52:01,534
Let's do it!

876
00:52:05,575 --> 00:52:07,333
You can tell one's mood...

877
00:52:08,067 --> 00:52:08,993
...thoughts...

878
00:52:09,345 --> 00:52:10,221
...and emotions easily....

879
00:52:10,566 --> 00:52:12,127
...through one's facial expression
as if you're looking into the mirror.

880
00:52:21,978 --> 00:52:22,877
Mom.

881
00:52:23,934 --> 00:52:25,732
Don't worry. I'm still in the bus.

882
00:52:27,334 --> 00:52:28,701
Can't you believe your daughter?

883
00:52:29,249 --> 00:52:31,150
Okay. Okay.

884
00:52:31,897 --> 00:52:33,997
I feel great.

885
00:52:34,280 --> 00:52:36,963
But you can also hide your mood...

886
00:52:37,167 --> 00:52:40,540
...thoughts, and feelings with your face
expressions like putting on a mask.

887
00:53:11,437 --> 00:53:14,402
But in the flash of a moment...

888
00:53:17,000 --> 00:53:18,415
...there's a moment where...

889
00:53:18,634 --> 00:53:20,502
...the boundary between that
mask and mirror comes down.

890
00:53:34,167 --> 00:53:35,924
The truth that no one saw...

891
00:53:47,362 --> 00:53:49,289
That feeling that you
didn't want others to see.

892
00:53:52,167 --> 00:53:54,609
The moment it surfaces
to the world for a moment...

893
00:53:58,033 --> 00:54:01,393
If we face that moment,
let's not close our eyes.

894
00:54:21,977 --> 00:54:23,146
Let's not ignore them if we see them.

895
00:54:24,252 --> 00:54:27,424
Let's not avoid them,
but let's face them.

896
00:54:48,267 --> 00:54:48,883
Hello.

897
00:54:48,968 --> 00:54:50,469
Nam Hongjoo has returned to work.

898
00:54:50,534 --> 00:54:51,435
It's been a long time.

899
00:54:51,534 --> 00:54:53,402
Welcome back, Nam Hongjoo.

900
00:54:53,501 --> 00:54:55,111
Welcome to hell.

901
00:54:55,734 --> 00:54:56,468
It's been a while.

902
00:54:56,553 --> 00:54:57,387
Yes.

903
00:54:58,004 --> 00:55:00,066
Captain. I've returned to work.

904
00:55:00,167 --> 00:55:01,347
Is your health better?

905
00:55:01,432 --> 00:55:02,601
It's nice to see you again.

906
00:55:02,701 --> 00:55:04,602
Congratulations on having a baby.

907
00:55:04,701 --> 00:55:05,768
Your eye make-up smeared.

908
00:55:05,853 --> 00:55:07,015
Don't you look at yourself in the mirror?

909
00:55:10,100 --> 00:55:11,901
I've returned to work.

910
00:55:12,000 --> 00:55:14,334
I put your uniform
on that desk over there.

911
00:55:18,994 --> 00:55:21,568
I guess you are her supervisor
since you took care of that.

912
00:55:21,653 --> 00:55:24,549
You don't act like
how you feel. You jerk.

913
00:55:24,634 --> 00:55:27,768
Captain. What are you doing?

914
00:55:28,334 --> 00:55:30,738
You're my supervisor,
but you don't even help me.

915
00:55:30,925 --> 00:55:33,325
What are you doing?

916
00:55:51,367 --> 00:55:54,148
We got a different design this time,
so our uniforms changed.

917
00:55:54,886 --> 00:55:58,176
I was sick of purple uniforms.
Try it on to see if it looks good.

918
00:56:03,189 --> 00:56:05,550
Is it that difficult to
cross the crosswalk?

919
00:56:06,247 --> 00:56:07,175
I know.

920
00:56:07,260 --> 00:56:08,901
Maybe it's because
I haven't been here in a while.

921
00:56:09,000 --> 00:56:11,151
It's hard and I'm nervous for no reason.

922
00:56:11,236 --> 00:56:12,161
Then what would you like me to do?

923
00:56:12,246 --> 00:56:14,013
Do you want me to go inside with you?

924
00:56:14,634 --> 00:56:15,734
What's wrong with you?

925
00:56:16,026 --> 00:56:17,711
I might start to misunderstand again.

926
00:56:17,901 --> 00:56:20,682
I might cling onto you and ask
you to take me to work every day.

927
00:56:20,767 --> 00:56:22,268
And whine to you about protecting me.

928
00:56:24,336 --> 00:56:25,250
Why don't you do that?

929
00:56:27,480 --> 00:56:28,047
Excuse me?

930
00:56:28,221 --> 00:56:32,079
Cling onto me, ask me to take
you to work and protect you.

931
00:56:32,567 --> 00:56:33,673
I'll give it a try.

932
00:56:37,067 --> 00:56:40,474
If that puts you at ease,
I'll give it a try.

933
00:56:43,799 --> 00:56:46,518
Why are you saying that?
It sounds like you mean it.

934
00:56:49,267 --> 00:56:50,968
I meant it.

935
00:56:51,221 --> 00:56:52,495
Don't you believe me?

936
00:56:52,667 --> 00:56:53,757
Is that why you're crying?

937
00:56:54,901 --> 00:56:56,458
I'm crying because I believe you.

938
00:56:56,909 --> 00:56:58,462
Because I feel relieved.

939
00:56:59,300 --> 00:57:01,290
I really wanted to hear those words.

940
00:57:02,540 --> 00:57:03,686
That's why I'm crying.

941
00:57:06,300 --> 00:57:08,971
My eye make-up has smeared.

942
00:57:12,152 --> 00:57:13,405
Excuse me.

943
00:57:13,963 --> 00:57:14,948
You said you'd protect me.

944
00:57:15,033 --> 00:57:16,475
Can't you at least do this for me?

945
00:57:30,361 --> 00:57:31,949
You're not avoiding it today.

946
00:58:33,767 --> 00:58:34,735
Don't you like it?

947
00:58:36,270 --> 00:58:37,222
No.

948
00:58:38,968 --> 00:58:40,538
I really like it.

949
00:59:37,307 --> 00:59:39,182
"While You Were Sleeping"

950
00:59:39,267 --> 00:59:40,834
Did you kill your younger brother?

951
00:59:42,124 --> 00:59:43,883
I'm asking you to make me innocent.

952
00:59:43,968 --> 00:59:45,836
The opposing attorney
is Lee Yoobum.

953
00:59:45,934 --> 00:59:47,768
He'll be found guilty by 99 percent.
Of course.

954
00:59:47,868 --> 00:59:48,849
We're the 99 percent.

955
00:59:48,934 --> 00:59:50,101
Your Honor, the defense council is...

956
00:59:50,192 --> 00:59:53,567
All of these records here are
denouncing the prosecution's claims.

957
00:59:53,652 --> 00:59:55,681
If he is released like that and kills more
people, you'll be the one responsible.

958
00:59:55,766 --> 00:59:58,836
You prosecutors are responsible
for not proving that he's guilty!

959
01:00:00,020 --> 01:00:01,921
Jung Jaechan!

960
01:00:09,200 --> 01:00:14,934
"While You Were Sleeping"
